I can attest to that. We just got it working using the romi template from the robotpy examples. Thank you for this!

It took a long time to read the romi docs only to realize that it is relatively simple to run, and you don’t need any driver station software or anything on the pi except the wpilib romi image. All communication to the romi goes through the sim interface.

To save others a bit of headache, pay attention to the comment in the robot.py that you have to pass the sim --ws-client:

python robot.py sim --ws-client

otherwise you will may spend an hour seeing that it works fine with Java and trying to figure out what went wrong. Many thanks to the wpilib team for the work on this. The students now have a much gentler way to practice with autonomous.
